com.github.mibac138.argparser.binder

Class JavaDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator

  • com.github.mibac138.argparser.binder.JavaDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SyntaxGenerator

    public class JavaDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator
implements SyntaxGenerator

    Basically a port of Kotlin's optional KParameters. When setting default values parsers should return them if they couldn't parse the input

    See Also:
    optional, KParameter

      static class  JavaDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator.NO_DEFAULT_VALUE
      Use this when you don't want the param to have a default value but want a next param (or any after this one) to have it

    • Constructor Detail

      • JavaDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator

        public JavaDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator(java.lang.Object defaultValues)
        Parameters:
        defaultValues - the array of default values. Must be in the same order as the method's parameters. In case you, e.g. want to have a default value for the 2nd parameter but not for the 1st then pass class JavaDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator.NO_DEFAULT_VALUE as the 1st default value
